 82: 
 83: ## 6. Workflow lessons (Part A of plan)
 84: 
 85: 8 patterns PM commits to going forward. Full table in `.user_bugs-log` and plan file at `C:\Users\ADMIN\.claude\plans\c-r-i-nh-gi-spicy-blum.md`.
 86: 
 87: 1. **Write→Bash pattern**: no multi-line `python -c`. Save `.py` then run.
 88: 2. **No subagents for MCP work**: subagents in this runtime don't inherit MCP. Do MCP in main session.
 89: 3. **EnterPlanMode for >5 Webflow writes**: plan first, get approval, then execute.
 90: 4. **Retry on bash error in same turn**: never end a turn on a failure without retry.
 91: 5. **Caveman terse for all messages >3 lines**: bullet list with `path:line` refs.
 92: 6. **Stop after first failure**: never stack two tool calls when the first errored.
 93: 7. **Surface stand-in swap path**: 1 line per decision showing how to replace.
 94: 8. **Blocker format**: include "tried: N times" + "next action" + "user vs PM-recoverable".
 95: 
 96: ## 7. Out of scope (user opt-in needed)
 97: 
 98: - Real asset uploads (16 Figma localhost images)
 99: - Webflow publish to live domain
100: - Custom domain config
101: - Google Analytics / tracking
102: - Localization
103: - Form / CMS wiring (none in this design)
104: - Per-element prop binding to CMS (none in this design — all static)
105: - A/B testing
106: - SEO metadata customization beyond what was set on `create_page` (title + description)
107: 
108: PM will not perform any of these without explicit user approval.
