<file path="agentic/memory/team-memory.md">
 1: # Team Memory
 2: 
 3: Keep this file concise. Archive older notes into `agentic/memory/archive/` when it grows beyond 200 lines.
 4: 
 5: ## What This Folder Is
 6: 
 7: This is a standalone Claude-native agentic folder for MAS V3: Figma to Webflow automation using a PM-led multi-agent workflow, Finsweet Client-First V2 rules, workspace JSON chunking, MCP-352 micro-chunking, and evidence-backed QA.
 8: 
 9: The existing files remain source-of-truth inputs:
10: 
11: - `agentic/policies/runtime-instructions.md`: original MAS V3 mandates adapted for Claude Code.
12: - `agentic/orchestration/sop.md`: four-phase workflow.
13: - `README.md`: user-facing system overview.
14: - `knowledge-base/client-first-theory.md`: Client-First theory.
15: - `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json`: structured Client-First class and Figma property mapping library.
16: - `scripts/*.py`: active Python workspace lifecycle tools and gates.
17: 
18: ## Hard Invariants
19: 
20: 1. Standalone baseline is mandatory: this folder must pass `agentic/evals/standalone-architecture-baseline.md`.
21: 2. Agent-system output is mandatory: `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md` records seed input, agent system spec, matrix, workflows, gates, and validation report.
22: 3. `@pm` is the only user-facing orchestrator.
23: 4. `@architect` owns blueprint logic and QA; it can reject builds.
24: 5. `@operator` owns Figma extraction and Webflow execution.
25: 6. `workspace/` is the operational state layer. Agents communicate through workspace artifacts, not hidden chat memory.
26: 7. Figma properties must map through `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` before class decisions enter a blueprint.
27: 8. Blueprint approval is a hard stop before Webflow build.
28: 9. No silent overwrite. Existing project files and workspace state are preserved unless a documented gate approves a transition.
29: 10. Webflow external writes are high risk and require explicit workflow phase, target site/page, payload summary, and validation evidence.
30: 11. Secrets belong outside committed files.
31: 
32: ## Agent Team
33: 
34: | Agent | Role | Default Access |
35: |---|---|---|
36: | `pm` | User-facing orchestrator and phase controller. | read, write plans, run safe gates |
37: | `client-first-architect` | Blueprint, Client-First class system, layout logic, QA rejection. | read, write blueprints, inspect Webflow |
38: | `figma-webflow-operator` | Figma extraction and Webflow native build execution. | read/write workspace, external Figma/Webflow when approved |
39: | `workspace-steward` | Archive, restore, state hygiene, handoff integrity. | read/write workspace lifecycle files |
40: | `qa-gatekeeper` | Deterministic validation, standalone baseline, final QA report. | read, run gates |
41: 
42: ## Current Status
43: 
44: This scaffold is self-contained. Run:
45: 
46: ```cmd
47: python scripts\gates\validate_agentic_structure.py --target .
48: python scripts\gates\run_quality_gate.py --target .
49: python scripts\gates\scan_secrets.py --target .
50: python scripts\gates\validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .
51: python scripts\gates\validate_skills.py --target .
52: python scripts\gates\validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .
53: python scripts\gates\validate_phase_state.py --target .
54: python scripts\gates\validate_relative_paths.py --target .
55: python scripts\gates\validate_client_first_library.py --target .
56: ```
57: 
58: ## Memory Promotion
59: 
60: Promote a memory only when it has:
61: 
62: - source file or command evidence,
63: - date,
64: - owner,
65: - validation status,
66: - reason it should persist.
</file>

