<file path="agentic/orchestration/phase-state-machine.md">
 1: # Phase State Machine
 2: 
 3: The PM controls phase movement. Workers can propose state changes, but only the PM records phase decisions.
 4: 
 5: ## States
 6: 
 7: | State | Entry Condition | Exit Condition |
 8: |---|---|---|
 9: | `phase_0_setup_audit` | New request or resumed workspace. | Workspace, handoff, MCP readiness, and target evidence are known. |
10: | `phase_1_blueprint` | Figma source or source substitute is accepted. | Blueprint exists and user approval is recorded. |
11: | `phase_2_webflow_build` | User approval exists for a specific blueprint version. | Webflow action log exists and QA is ready. (Single-operator path or umbrella for 2A/2B.) |
12: | `phase_2a_class_setup` | User approval exists; build-contract gate passes. | All `new_classes` created and registered; all section containers created with node IDs. |
13: | `phase_2b_parallel_section_build` | Phase 2A complete (classes + containers exist). | All section action logs present and ready for QA. |
14: | `phase_3_qa_loop` | Build or fix action is complete. | QA verdict is `[APPROVED]` or unresolved blockers are documented. |
15: | `handoff_closeout` | Phase completes or session ends. | `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md` is updated. |
16: 
17: ## Allowed Transitions
18: 
19: ```text
20: phase_0_setup_audit -> phase_1_blueprint
21: phase_1_blueprint -> phase_2_webflow_build
22: phase_1_blueprint -> phase_2a_class_setup
23: phase_2a_class_setup -> phase_2b_parallel_section_build
24: phase_2b_parallel_section_build -> phase_3_qa_loop
25: phase_2_webflow_build -> phase_3_qa_loop
26: phase_3_qa_loop -> phase_2_webflow_build
27: phase_3_qa_loop -> phase_2b_parallel_section_build
28: phase_3_qa_loop -> handoff_closeout
29: any_phase -> handoff_closeout
30: ```
31: 
32: The parallel-section path (`phase_2a_class_setup -> phase_2b_parallel_section_build`) and the
33: single-operator path (`phase_2_webflow_build`) are alternatives. Both require the same approval gate.
34: 
35: ## Approval Rule
36: 
37: `phase_1_blueprint -> phase_2_webflow_build` and `phase_1_blueprint -> phase_2a_class_setup` are both blocked unless `workspace/state.json` contains an approval entry with:
38: 
39: - `type`: `approval`
40: - `phase`: `phase_1_blueprint`
41: - `artifact`: the approved blueprint path
42: - `message`: contains `Approved`
43: - `approver`: `user`
44: 
45: ## ReAct Rule
46: 
47: Every Webflow mutation in `phase_2_webflow_build` must record:
48: 
49: - `reason`
50: - `action`
51: - `observation`
52: - `next_decision`
53: 
54: This keeps tool use auditable and prevents build steps from becoming unexplained mutations.
</file>

<file path="agentic/orchestration/reflection-loop.md">
 1: # Reflection Loop
 2: 
 3: The MAS workflow uses reflection as a bounded review loop before any risky Webflow action is treated as complete.
 4: 
 5: ## Loop Contract
 6: 
 7: | Step | Owner | Action | Output |
 8: |---|---|---|---|
 9: | Draft | `figma-webflow-operator` or `client-first-architect` | Produce blueprint, build log, or QA report. | Candidate artifact in `workspace/`. |
10: | Critique | `qa-gatekeeper` or `client-first-architect` | Score against the reflection rubric and current evidence. | `reflection_review` entry in `workspace/state.json`. |
11: | Revise | Original producer | Apply only the cited fixes. | New artifact version or appended fix entry. |
12: | Decide | `pm` | Accept, request another loop, or escalate. | Phase status and handoff update. |
13: 
14: ## Required Reflection Entry
15: 
16: ```json
17: {
18:   "type": "reflection_review",
19:   "agent": "qa-gatekeeper",
20:   "phase": "phase_1_blueprint",
21:   "artifact": "workspace/blueprints/home.json",
22:   "score": 4.6,
23:   "verdict": "revise",
24:   "findings": [
25:     {
26:       "criterion": "Client-First structure",
27:       "severity": "major",
28:       "evidence": "Hero wrapper and content wrapper are merged.",
29:       "required_fix": "Split section, container, and component layers."
30:     }
31:   ],
32:   "next_decision": "route_to_architect"
33: }
34: ```
35: 
36: ## Stop Conditions
37: 
38: - Pass when the artifact reaches the phase threshold in `agentic/evals/reflection-rubric.md`.
39: - Stop and escalate after two failed reflection loops on the same issue.
40: - Stop immediately if the critique lacks evidence paths, screenshots, state references, or Webflow/Figma observations.
41: - Never convert a reflection pass into Webflow approval. The phase approval gate still applies.
</file>

<file path="agentic/orchestration/retry-and-stop-conditions.md">
 1: # Retry and Stop Conditions
 2: 
 3: | Workflow | Retry Limit | Stop Conditions |
 4: |---|---:|---|
 5: | workspace init | 1 | workspace exists and required files exist, or script failure. |
 6: | archive workspace | 1 | archive missing/empty, explicit user cancellation, or successful wipe. |
 7: | restore workspace | 1 | workspace non-empty, archive missing, or successful restore. |
 8: | Figma extraction | 2 | raw/content files created, Figma auth failure, missing URL/node. |
 9: | blueprint creation | 2 | blueprint ready for approval, missing raw data, unresolved design ambiguity. |
10: | Webflow build | 3 | MCP-352 verification boundary, tool failure, target mismatch, QA needed. |
11: | class + container setup (Phase 2A) | 1 | all classes created and registered + containers created, or tool failure (deterministic, no backoff). |
12: | section build per subagent (Phase 2B) | 3 | section subtree matches contract, MCP-352 boundary, missing class blocker, or tool failure. |
13: | parallel QA aggregation | 2 | all section logs reconciled vs blueprint, or a section needs a fix loop. |
14: | QA loop | 5 | `[APPROVED]`, repeated same blocker, missing Webflow evidence. |
15: 
16: If the same blocker repeats three times, PM records it in `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md` and asks for the missing external state or decision.
</file>

<file path="agentic/orchestration/sop.md">
  1: # Standard Operating Procedure
  2: 
  3: This SOP governs the Claude Code-native, Python-first MAS Figma-to-Webflow workflow.
  4: 
  5: ## Phase 0: Setup and Audit
  6: 
  7: Goal: synchronize state and protect the Webflow site and local workspace.
  8: 
  9: 1. PM reads:
 10:    - `CLAUDE.md`
 11:    - `agentic/memory/team-memory.md`
 12:    - `agentic/policies/runtime-instructions.md`
 13:    - `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md`
 14:    - `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md`
 15: 2. Workspace steward validates or initializes workspace:
 16: 
 17: ```cmd
 18: python scripts\init_workspace.py --project "Project Name" --figma "Figma URL"
 19: ```
 20: 
 21: 3. If changing projects, steward must archive first:
 22: 
 23: ```cmd
 24: python scripts\archive_workspace.py
 25: ```
 26: 
 27: 4. Before restoring, steward must confirm `workspace/` is empty:
 28: 
 29: ```cmd
 30: python scripts\restore_workspace.py 0
 31: ```
 32: 
 33: 5. Operator verifies target Figma and Webflow scope when connectors are configured.
 34: 6. PM records blockers and current phase in `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md`.
 35: 
 36: Stop conditions:
 37: 
 38: - missing Figma URL,
 39: - missing Webflow site/page target,
 40: - non-empty workspace before restore,
 41: - archive validation failure,
 42: - missing approval for external access.
 43: 
 44: ## Phase 1: Blueprint Establishment
 45: 
 46: Goal: produce Client-First blueprints and isolate data.
 47: 
 48: 1. Operator extracts raw Figma data into:
 49:    - `workspace/rawdata/[section_id]_raw.json`
 50:    - `workspace/contents/[section_id]_content.json`
 51: 2. Architect reads:
 52:    - `knowledge-base/client-first-theory.md`
 53:    - `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json`
 54:    - `agentic/specs/figma-to-client-first-mapping.md`
 55:    - raw data,
 56:    - content data,
 57:    - `workspace/design-system.json`
 58: 3. Produce design analysis: run `agentic/prompts/read-figma-data.md` prompt to output `workspace/blueprints/[page-slug]_design-analysis.json` from Figma raw data. Validate all color tokens and layout patterns before proceeding.
 59: 4. Architect writes:
 60:    - `workspace/blueprints/[section_id]_blueprint.json`
 61:    - updates to `workspace/page_structure.json`
 62: 5. PM presents blueprint to the user.
 63: 6. PM stops until the user says `Approved` or `Agree`.
 64: 
 65: Hard rules:
 66: 
 67: - `page-wrapper` and `main-wrapper` must be accounted for.
 68: - Global components cannot be vague stand-ins.
 69: - Every class mapping must cite the Client-First class map.
 70: - `page_structure.json` stores routing/index data, not raw Figma data.
 71: - All spacing and sizes use rem.
 72: 
 73: ## Phase 2: Webflow Execution
 74: 
 75: Goal: execute only the approved blueprint with Webflow native operations.
 76: 
 77: Preconditions (all of Phase 2):
 78: 
 79: - user approval exists,
 80: - Webflow site/page target confirmed,
 81: - approved blueprint path exists,
 82: - operator has a scoped task.
 83: 
 84: MCP-352 (applies to every Webflow turn, parent and subagent):
 85: 
 86: - max 3 nesting levels per turn,
 87: - max 5 Webflow actions per turn,
 88: - verify state after every 2 successful actions.
 89: 
 90: Forbidden:
 91: 
 92: - no `whtml_builder` (the blueprint `html_contract` is an instruction, recreated with native ops),
 93: - no unapproved Webflow writes,
 94: - no real asset uploads by default,
 95: - no silent creation of pages/components.
 96: 
 97: The build runs as two sub-phases. A single-section page may collapse 2A and 2B into one operator pass.
 98: 
 99: ### Phase 2A: Class and Container Setup (serial, parent)
100: 
101: Run by the parent operator. This is the only place classes are created, which removes the
102: parallel naming race.
103: 
104: 1. Run the build-contract gate before any write:
105: 
106: ```cmd
107: python scripts\gates\validate_build_contract.py --site-id <webflow_site_id>
108: ```
109: 
110: 2. For each entry in the blueprint `new_classes`, create the class on Webflow with the native
111:    `style_tool`, then register it into `knowledge-base/libraries/{site_id}/client-first-library.json`
112:    and append a `changelog.json` entry (`source: "figma_adapt"`).
113: 3. Create the N section container elements under `main-wrapper` in correct vertical order.
114: 4. Record each container's returned `{component, element}` object as the section's
115:    `target_parent_element_id`, logged to `workspace/state.json` under phase `phase_2a_class_setup`.
116:    This object is passed directly as `parent_element_id` to `element_builder` in Phase 2B.
117: 
118: Exit: all `new_classes` exist on Webflow and are registered; all section containers created with `parent_element_id` objects.
119: 
120: ### Phase 2B: Parallel Section Build
121: 
122: Run by one `section-builder` subagent per section (apply-only).
123: 
124: 1. PM builds a `subagent-task` payload per section (see `agentic/schemas/subagent-task.schema.json`).
125: 2. PM spawns one `section-builder` per section. Spawn in parallel when the Webflow MCP supports
126:    concurrent writes to one site; otherwise the same payloads run sequentially. Correctness is identical.
127: 3. Each subagent recreates its `html_contract` under its `parent_element_id` with native operations,
128:    applies existing classes only, and never creates classes, pages, or components.
129: 4. Each subagent logs to `workspace/sections/[section_id]_action_log.json`.
130: 
131: Exit: all section action logs present and ready for QA.
132: 
133: Output:
134: 
135: - action entries in `workspace/state.json` and `workspace/sections/[section_id]_action_log.json`,
136: - blockers in `workspace/error-logs.json`.
137: 
138: ## Phase 3: QA Loop
139: 
140: Goal: verify 1:1 Webflow output against Figma and Client-First blueprint.
141: 
142: 1. Architect inspects actual Webflow state or snapshots.
143: 2. Architect compares:
144:    - hierarchy,
145:    - classes,
146:    - spacing,
147:    - typography,
148:    - responsive layout,
149:    - component behavior.
150: 3. Architect writes `[APPROVED]` or `[FIX]`.
151: 4. PM routes fixes to operator and repeats QA when needed.
152: 5. Gatekeeper runs local gates:
153: 
154: ```cmd
155: python scripts\gates\validate_agentic_structure.py --target .
156: python scripts\gates\run_quality_gate.py --target .
157: python scripts\gates\scan_secrets.py --target .
158: python scripts\gates\validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .
159: python scripts\gates\validate_skills.py --target .
160: python scripts\gates\validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .
161: python scripts\gates\validate_phase_state.py --target .
162: python scripts\gates\validate_relative_paths.py --target .
163: python scripts\gates\validate_client_first_library.py --target .
164: ```
165: 
166: Completion requires:
167: 
168: - QA evidence,
169: - passing local gates,
170: - updated `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md`,
171: - evidence-backed final report.
</file>

