<file path="agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md">
  1: # Agent System Spec
  2: 
  3: ## Summary
  4: 
  5: MAS-Figma-Webflow-khang is a standalone Claude-native, Python-first agentic folder for converting Figma designs into Webflow builds using MAS V3 orchestration, Finsweet Client-First V2 rules, structured class mapping, workspace JSON chunking, MCP-352 micro-chunking, reflection, and strict QA.
  6: 
  7: ## Seed Input
  8: 
  9: ```json
 10: {
 11:   "idea": "Create an AI agentic folder that coordinates PM, architect, and operator agents to convert Figma designs into Webflow pages with Client-First quality.",
 12:   "jobs_to_be_done": [
 13:     "Initialize and preserve project workspace state",
 14:     "Extract Figma raw data and content into chunked workspace files",
 15:     "Produce Client-First Webflow blueprints",
 16:     "Run user approval before Webflow execution",
 17:     "Build in Webflow with native element operations and MCP-352",
 18:     "Run pixel-perfect QA and fix loops",
 19:     "Record evidence, handoff state, and validation reports"
 20:   ],
 21:   "domain": "Figma to Webflow implementation",
 22:   "target_runtime": "claude_code",
 23:   "stack": ["python", "powershell", "webflow-mcp", "figma-source-data"],
 24:   "risk_level": "high",
 25:   "reference_repos": [
 26:     "webflow/webflow-skills",
 27:     "OneWave-AI/claude-skills"
 28:   ],
 29:   "embedded_standards": [
 30:     "standalone_architecture_baseline",
 31:     "agent_system_spec_contract",
 32:     "client_first_class_library",
 33:     "reflection_react_contract",
 34:     "visual_qa_evidence_contract"
 35:   ],
 36:   "required_tools": ["git", "python", "figma", "webflow-mcp"],
 37:   "constraints": [
 38:     "no silent overwrite",
 39:     "no Webflow external write without approval",
 40:     "no whtml_builder",
 41:     "MCP-352 required",
 42:     "REM units only",
 43:     "Client-First V2 structure required",
 44:     "Client-First class mapping library required",
 45:     "workspace JSON evidence required"
 46:   ],
 47:   "success_criteria": [
 48:     "standalone architecture baseline passes",
 49:     "Client-First library gate passes",
 50:     "agent_system_spec contains agents, skills, tools, MCP servers, workflows, memory, gates, scaffold files, and validation report",
 51:     "structure, quality, skill, workspace, phase, path, library, and secret gates pass",
 52:     "PM can run the four SOP phases from one user request"
 53:   ]
 54: }
 55: ```
 56: 
 57: ## Agents
 58: 
 59: | Agent | Role | Trigger | Allowed Tools | Forbidden Actions | Output |
 60: |---|---|---|---|---|---|
 61: | `pm` | User-facing orchestrator and phase controller. | Any user request or phase transition. | Read, write plans/handoff, run safe gates. | Bypass approval, direct Webflow writes, direct QA approval. | Phase report, task requests, handoff. |
 62: | `client-first-architect` | Blueprint and QA owner. | Phase 1 blueprint or Phase 3 QA. | Read/write blueprints, inspect Webflow evidence. | Build in Webflow, approve without evidence. | Blueprint JSON, QA verdict. |
 63: | `figma-webflow-operator` | Figma extraction and Webflow execution. | Phase 1 extraction, Phase 2 build, fix loops. | Read/write workspace, external Figma/Webflow when approved. | Use `whtml_builder`, exceed MCP-352, mutate unknown targets. | Raw/content JSON, state log. |
 64: | `workspace-steward` | Workspace lifecycle and handoff integrity. | Archive, restore, init, page transition. | Workspace scripts and handoff updates. | Delete unarchived state, restore into non-empty workspace. | Lifecycle report. |
 65: | `qa-gatekeeper` | Deterministic gates and standalone readiness. | After scaffold/build/QA report. | Read and run gates. | Edit producer artifacts, mark unchecked gates as pass. | Validation report. |
 66: | `section-builder` | Apply-only build of one section subtree under a given parent node. | Phase 2B parallel section build, one per section. | Native Webflow ops confined to `parent_node_id`, write section action log. | Use `whtml_builder`, create classes/pages/components, write outside its subtree, exceed MCP-352. | Section action log. |
 67: 
 68: ## Skills
 69: 
 70: | Skill | Purpose | Validation |
 71: |---|---|---|
 72: | `figma-to-webflow-build` | Run the full MAS V3 workflow. | Gate results and handoff update. |
 73: | `client-first-blueprint` | Produce Client-First blueprints from Figma data. | Blueprint evidence and Client-First checks. |
 74: | `mcp-352-webflow-build` | Build in Webflow using native micro-chunks. | State log and QA evidence. |
 75: | `parallel-section-build` | Orchestrate Phase 2A class/container setup then Phase 2B per-section subagents. | Build-contract gate pass and aggregated section logs. |
 76: | `pixel-perfect-qa` | Validate Webflow output against Figma/blueprint. | `[APPROVED]` or `[FIX]` with evidence. |
 77: | `reflection-review` | Critique risky artifacts with a bounded reflection loop. | Pass, revise, or block with score and evidence. |
 78: 
 79: ## Tools
 80: 
 81: | Tool | Purpose | risk_class | approval_policy | auth_requirements | allowed_agents |
 82: |---|---|---|---|---|---|
 83: | `Read/Grep/Glob` | Local inspection. | R0 | allow | none | all agents |
 84: | `Write/Edit` | Create specs, workspace files, reports. | R1 | ask/create-only | none | pm, architect, operator, steward |
 85: | `python scripts/init_workspace.py` | Initialize workspace. | R1 | ask | none | workspace-steward, pm |
 86: | `python scripts/archive_workspace.py` | Archive and wipe workspace after zip validation. | R4 | explicit approval | none | workspace-steward |
 87: | `python scripts/restore_workspace.py` | Restore archived workspace. | R4 | explicit approval | none | workspace-steward |
 88: | `python scripts/gates/*.py` | Deterministic validation. | R0 | allow | none | qa-gatekeeper, pm |
 89: | `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` | Structured Figma property to Client-First class mapping. | R0 | allow read | none | architect, operator, gatekeeper |
 90: | `Figma API/MCP` | Extract design data. | R2 | ask | Figma token or approved connector | figma-webflow-operator |
 91: | `Webflow MCP` | Inspect and mutate Webflow site. | R3 | explicit approval for writes | Webflow auth | operator, architect for read/QA |
 92: 
 93: ## MCP Servers
 94: 
 95: | Server | Purpose | risk_class | approval_policy | auth_requirements | allowed_agents | config_path |
 96: |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
 97: | `webflow` | Webflow inspect/build operations through Claude Code MCP after auth setup. | R3 | ask; writes require explicit phase approval | Webflow OAuth/session | operator, architect read/QA | `agentic/policies/mcp-config.example.json` example |
 98: | `filesystem` | Local project file access. | R0/R1 | allow read, ask write | none | all agents by role | `agentic/policies/mcp-config.example.json` |
 99: | `figma` | Figma data extraction if configured. | R2 | ask | Figma token/OAuth | operator | documented skip until configured |
100: 
101: ## Workflows
102: 
103: | Workflow | Trigger | Outputs | retry_limit | stop_conditions | validation_gate |
104: |---|---|---|---:|---|---|
105: | `phase_0_setup_audit` | New project or resumed session. | workspace audit, handoff update. | 2 | missing auth/target, unsafe workspace state. | structure + quality gate |
106: | `phase_1_blueprint` | Figma target confirmed. | raw/content data, blueprint JSON with class mapping. | 2 | blueprint ready for approval, missing Figma data. | blueprint review + client-first library |
107: | `phase_2_webflow_build` | User approves blueprint. | Webflow state changes, ReAct action log. | 3 | MCP-352 boundary, Webflow failure, QA needed. | state log + phase gate |
108: | `phase_3_qa_loop` | Build or fix complete. | `[APPROVED]` or `[FIX]`. | 5 | approved, unresolved blocker, repeated failure. | pixel-perfect QA + reflection |
109: | `handoff_closeout` | Phase complete or session ending. | updated `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md`. | 1 | handoff complete. | quality gate |
110: 
111: ## Memory
112: 
113: | Path | kind | owner | promotion_rule |
114: |---|---|---|---|
115: | `agentic/knowledge/project-overview.md` | durable knowledge | pm | update when project architecture changes |
116: | `agentic/knowledge/system-map.md` | durable knowledge | pm | update when workflow/files change |
117: | `agentic/knowledge/client-first-library.md` | durable knowledge | architect | update when class mapping rules change |
118: | `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` | structured library | architect | update only with source and gate validation |
119: | `agentic/memory/memory-candidates.md` | candidate memory | all agents | promote only with source, date, validation |
120: | `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md` | operational memory | pm | update every phase boundary |
121: | `workspace/state.json` | runtime log | operator | generated evidence, not durable memory |
122: 
123: ## Gates
124: 
125: | Gate | command_or_rule | scope | pass_condition |
126: |---|---|---|---|
127: | structure | `python scripts/gates/validate_agentic_structure.py --target .` | repo scaffold | required standalone paths exist |
128: | quality | `python scripts/gates/run_quality_gate.py --target .` | docs/specs | mandatory phrases and policies present |
129: | secrets | `python scripts/gates/scan_secrets.py --target .` | committed files | no common secret patterns |
130: | system spec | `python scripts/gates/validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .` | system spec | required spec sections present |
131: | skill anatomy | `python scripts/gates/validate_skills.py --target .` | Claude skills | frontmatter, workflow, validation, and resource folders exist |
132: | workspace artifacts | `python scripts/gates/validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .` | generated workspace | JSON and ReAct action entries are valid when workspace exists |
133: | phase state | `python scripts/gates/validate_phase_state.py --target .` | runtime phase log | phase 2 cannot start without user approval |
134: | relative paths | `python scripts/gates/validate_relative_paths.py --target .` | repo content | no local absolute filesystem paths |
135: | Client-First library | `python scripts/gates/validate_client_first_library.py --target .` | class catalog | structured class groups and mapping rules exist |
136: | approval | policy check | workflow | external write has target, payload summary, and approval |
137: 
