<file path="agentic/specs/figma-to-client-first-mapping.md">
  1: # Figma to Client-First Mapping
  2: 
  3: This contract turns Figma properties into Client-First class decisions. It prevents the architect and operator from inventing one-off classes when a reusable Client-First class or variable should be used.
  4: 
  5: ## Mapping Pipeline
  6: 
  7: | Step | Input | Decision | Output |
  8: |---|---|---|---|
  9: | Identify role | Frame name, hierarchy, component context | Page wrapper, section, component, child, or utility wrapper. | `element_role` |
 10: | Read properties | Auto-layout, fills, strokes, typography, variant, size | Select matching rule from `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json`. | `class_mapping[]` |
 11: | Normalize units | Pixel-like values | Convert to REM and token size. | `rem_value` |
 12: | Pick strategy | Global, utility, custom, combo, variable-backed utility | Decide class application mode. | `class_strategy` |
 13: | Write blueprint | Mapped classes and reasons | Build-ready class contract. | `workspace/blueprints/*.json` |
 14: 
 15: ## Blueprint Class Mapping Shape
 16: 
 17: ```json
 18: {
 19:   "element_id": "figma-node-hero-title",
 20:   "element_role": "heading",
 21:   "class_mapping": [
 22:     {
 23:       "figma_property": "fontSize",
 24:       "figma_value": "64px",
 25:       "client_first_class": "heading-style-h1",
 26:       "webflow_property": "font-size",
 27:       "class_strategy": "utility_selection",
 28:       "reason": "Hero title is visually H1 scale.",
 29:       "source": "knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json"
 30:     }
 31:   ]
 32: }
 33: ```
 34: 
 35: ## Selection Rules
 36: 
 37: - Use `page-wrapper` and `main-wrapper` once per page.
 38: - Use `section_[name]` for every major page band.
 39: - Use `padding-global` for site gutters, not for local component padding.
 40: - Use `container-[size]` for centered max-width content.
 41: - Use `padding-section-[size]` for top and bottom section rhythm.
 42: - Use typography utilities for reusable type styling.
 43: - Use color utilities only when the color is mapped to a Webflow variable.
 44: - Use `[component]_[element]` for layout decisions that are unique to a section or component.
 45: - Use `is-[state]` only as a combo class on top of a base class.
 46: 
 47: ## Rejection Rules
 48: 
 49: Reject a blueprint when:
 50: 
 51: - it uses a custom class where an existing Client-First utility should be used,
 52: - it maps a Figma property without a reason,
 53: - it uses pixel units in the final Webflow property,
 54: - it skips source attribution to the class map,
 55: - it applies a Webflow class that has not been confirmed or created through the approved build path.
 56: 
 57: ---
 58: 
 59: ## Section A — Figma Node Type → HTML Tag
 60: 
 61: | Figma Node Type | Condition | HTML Tag | CF Class Pattern |
 62: |---|---|---|---|
 63: | FRAME | outermost page composition | `<div>` | `page-wrapper` |
 64: | FRAME | named "main" / "content" / wraps all sections | `<main>` | `main-wrapper` |
 65: | FRAME | large vertical band (hero, features, pricing, etc.) | `<section>` | `section_[slug]` |
 66: | FRAME | named "nav" / "navbar" / "navigation" | `<nav>` | custom `nav_component` |
 67: | FRAME | named "footer" | `<footer>` | custom `footer_component` |
 68: | FRAME | named "header" within a section | `<header>` | custom `[section]_header` |
 69: | COMPONENT INSTANCE | button component | `<a>` or `<button>` | `button` + combo |
 70: | COMPONENT INSTANCE | card/tile component | `<article>` if self-contained | custom `[comp]_card` |
 71: | FRAME with `clipsContent: true` + image fill | image mask | `<div>` | custom `[comp]_image-wrapper` + `overflow-hidden` |
 72: | TEXT | sole H1 on page | `<h1>` | no heading-style class needed |
 73: | TEXT | heading with semantic mismatch | `<h2>` (semantic) | + `heading-style-h3` (visual) |
 74: | TEXT | body paragraph | `<p>` | `text-size-*` utilities |
 75: | TEXT | inline variation | `<span>` | `text-style-*` utilities |
 76: | TEXT | list item | `<li>` | custom `[comp]_list-item` |
 77: | VECTOR / SVG < 64px | icon | `<img>` or `<svg>` | `icon-1x1-[size]` |
 78: | GROUP | layout grouping | `<div>` | custom `[section]_[role]` — ALWAYS custom (Case 1) |
 79: 
 80: Slugify rule: lowercase, spaces→hyphens, drop special chars. "Hero Section" → `hero`.
 81: 
 82: ---
 83: 
 84: ## Section B — Auto-Layout → Layout Decision
 85: 
 86: CF V2.2 ships real layout utilities. Use them first; custom class only as fallback.
 87: 
 88: | Figma Auto-Layout | Preferred CF utility | Custom class when |
 89: |---|---|---|
 90: | `direction: HORIZONTAL` + itemSpacing | `flex-horizontal` + `gap-[token]` | Need unique alignment, responsive reflow, or sizing not expressible by flex alone |
 91: | `direction: VERTICAL` + itemSpacing | `flex-vertical` + `gap-[token]` | Same — unique constraints only |
 92: | Multi-column grid (equal columns, N=1–6) | `grid-N-col` (+ `-tab`/`-mobile` for responsive) | > 6 columns, asymmetric columns, complex track sizes |
 93: | Auto-fill/auto-fit responsive grid | `grid-autofit-[size]` or `grid-autofill-[size]` | Custom min-width needed |
 94: | `layoutWrap: WRAP` | `flex-horizontal` + `flex-wrap-down` | — |
 95: | No auto-layout, absolute children | position:relative on parent (custom class) + `layer` on full-cover child | Always custom for positioning |
 96: 
 97: **Gap token selection:** Look up Figma itemSpacing in the Layout/Spacing or Layout/Gaps token scale.
 98: Pick the nearest token name (tiny/xxsmall/.../xxhuge or small/regular/medium/large for semantic gaps).
 99: Apply `gap-[token]` utility. Do NOT compute px/16 for literal rem — the variable handles responsive shift.
100: 
101: **When to create a custom class instead of using layout utilities:**
102: - Element needs unique width/height constraints on layout children
103: - 7+ column grids or complex CSS grid track definitions
104: - Absolute positioning with specific top/left/right/bottom offsets (not full-cover)
105: 
106: ## Section B2 — Responsive Strategy in CF V2.2
107: 
108: Spacing, typography, and grid gap responsive shifts are handled by **variable collection modes**,
109: not per-breakpoint utility classes. The Layout collection has Tablet and Mobile Landscape modes
110: that automatically change spacing values. The Typography collection has Tablet and Mobile Landscape
111: modes that shift heading font sizes.
112: 
113: **Consequence for HTML contract writing:**
114: - Do NOT create a custom class just to override spacing at tablet/mobile — the utility class handles it.
115: - Do NOT add `hide-tablet` + a custom class for spacing — just apply the spacing utility.
116: - Only create breakpoint custom classes for TRUE structural reflow: column count (use `grid-N-col-tab`),
117:   hide/show (`hide-tablet`), or complex layout changes that utilities can't express.
118: 
119: ---
120: 
121: **Spacing: token-snap, not px/16 math.**
122: Look at the Figma spacing/gap/padding value. Find the nearest Layout token in the scale
123: (none→0, tiny→0.125, xxsmall→0.25, xsmall→0.5, small→1, medium→2, large→3, xlarge→4, xxlarge→5,
124: huge→6, xhuge→8, xxhuge→12 rem on desktop). Apply that utility class. The variable automatically
125: provides tablet and mobile-landscape responsive values — no breakpoint custom class needed.
126: Exception: border sizes use explicit values (thin=1px, normal=0.125rem, bold=0.25rem).
127: 
128: ## Section C — Container Size Selection (project heuristic — real CF V2.2 values: container-small 48rem, container-medium 64rem, container-large 80rem)
129: 
130: Pick `container-[size]` by comparing content frame max-width:
131: 
132: | Figma content frame max-width | CF class |
133: |---|---|
134: | >= 1200px | `container-large` |
135: | 900px–1199px | `container-medium` |
136: | < 900px | `container-small` |
137: | No explicit max-width frame found | default `container-large` |
138: 
139: ---
140: 
141: ## Section D — Padding-Section Size Selection (project heuristic — real CF V2.2 values: section-small 3rem, section-medium 5rem, section-large 8rem desktop)
142: 
143: Pick `padding-section-[size]` from section vertical padding (top + bottom combined):
144: 
145: | Section top+bottom padding combined | CF class |
146: |---|---|
147: | >= 120px | `padding-section-large` |
148: | 64px–119px | `padding-section-medium` |
149: | < 64px | `padding-section-small` |
150: 
151: ---
152: 
153: ## Section E — Typography Matching Algorithm
154: 
155: For each TEXT node in Figma:
156: 
157: 1. Is this the ONLY h1-level heading on the page? → Use `<h1>` tag alone. No `heading-style-*` class needed (tag IS the style).
158: 2. Does the Figma text style name contain "Heading" / "H1"–"H6"?
159:    - Determine visual level (H1=largest, H6=smallest by font-size).
160:    - Determine semantic level needed for SEO/accessibility.
161:    - If visual level matches semantic level → use semantic tag alone.
162:    - If mismatch (e.g., SEO needs `<h2>` but visual = H3 size) → `<h2 class="heading-style-h3">`.
163: 3. Body text: compare fontSize to project scale in `workspace/design-system.json`; map to `text-size-[token]`.
164: 4. Font weight mapping:
165:    - 100–300 → `text-weight-light`
166:    - 400 → no class (if default body weight); otherwise `text-weight-normal`
167:    - 500 → `text-weight-medium`
168:    - 600 → `text-weight-semibold`
169:    - 700 → `text-weight-bold`
170:    - 800+ → `text-weight-xbold`
171: 5. Color: if fill references a Figma variable → use `text-color-[token]` from per-project library.
172: 6. Decoration/case:
173:    - `textDecoration: STRIKETHROUGH` → `text-style-strikethrough`
174:    - `textCase: UPPER` → `text-style-allcaps`
175:    - `fontStyle: Italic` → `text-style-italic`
176: 7. Multi-line clamp: 2-line truncation → `text-style-2lines`; 3-line → `text-style-3lines`.
177: 
178: ---
179: 
180: ## Section F — Figma Variable → Color Class
181: 
182: 1. All Figma color variables are listed in raw data under `"variables"` or `"variableCollections"`.
183: 2. For each variable used on a node, look up `figma_token` in `knowledge-base/libraries/{site_id}/client-first-library.json`.
184: 3. Apply the correct class by context:
185:    - Fill on TEXT node → `text-color-[token]`
186:    - Fill on FRAME (not text) → `background-color-[token]`
187:    - Stroke on FRAME/RECTANGLE → `border-color-[token]`
188: 4. Variable NOT in library → STOP. Request library update before writing HTML contract.
189: 5. Never hardcode hex values. Every color must trace back to a library class.
190: 
191: ---
192: 
193: ## Section G — Custom Class Naming from Figma Layer Names
194: 
195: 1. Section prefix = slugified Figma section frame name:
196:    - "Hero Section" → `hero`
197:    - "Feature Cards Grid" → `feature-cards`
198: 2. Element name = slugified Figma child layer name:
199:    - "Content Row" → `content-row`
200:    - "Image Wrapper" → `image-wrapper`
201:    - "CTA Button" → `cta-btn`
202: 3. Combined: `[section-prefix]_[element-name]`
203:    - `hero_content-row`, `feature-cards_image-wrapper`
204: 4. Generic layer names ("Group 1", "Frame 23") → infer from content type:
205:    - Contains only text nodes → `[section]_text-block`
206:    - Contains image/vector → `[section]_image-wrapper`
207:    - Horizontal row of children → `[section]_content-row`
208:    - Grid/list of repeated items → `[section]_grid`
209:    - Background decoration → `[section]_bg-layer`
210: 5. Page-specific elements (appear only on this page) → add page slug prefix: `home-hero_content-row`
211: 6. Global/reusable elements (shared across pages) → no page prefix: `card_wrapper`, `faq_item`
212: 7. Never apply a page-prefixed class to elements on other pages.
213: 
214: **`_component` wrapper convention (CF V2.2):**
215: - The outermost wrapper of a reusable component = `[name]_component` (e.g. `nav_component`, `form_component`)
216: - Direct children = `[name]_[element]` (e.g. `nav_brand`, `nav_menu`)
217: - Nested multi-level = `[name]_[parent]_[element]` (e.g. `nav_menu_link`)
218: - `fs-styleguide_*` classes = demo/styleguide only — NEVER use in builds
</file>

