<file path="README.md">
  1: # MAS Figma to Webflow for Claude Code
  2: 
  3: This folder is a Claude Code-native, Python-first agentic workflow for converting Figma designs into Webflow pages with Finsweet Client-First V2 quality.
  4: 
  5: It now carries its own standalone architecture baseline, agent-system contract, gates, schemas, and Client-First class library so it can be used as an independent repo.
  6: 
  7: ## Runtime
  8: 
  9: - Primary agent CLI: Claude Code.
 10: - Primary automation language: Python.
 11: - External execution: Webflow MCP and Figma connector only when explicitly approved.
 12: 
 13: ## Agent Team
 14: 
 15: | Agent | Role |
 16: |---|---|
 17: | `pm` | User-facing orchestrator. Reads the request, controls SOP phases, delegates to specialists, reports evidence. |
 18: | `client-first-architect` | Designs Client-First blueprints and performs QA rejection/approval. |
 19: | `figma-webflow-operator` | Extracts Figma data and executes approved Webflow builds. |
 20: | `workspace-steward` | Protects workspace lifecycle, archive, restore, and handoff state. |
 21: | `qa-gatekeeper` | Runs deterministic gates and standalone readiness checks. |
 22: 
 23: Agent definitions live in `.claude/agents/`.
 24: 
 25: ## Core Workflow
 26: 
 27: ```mermaid
 28: sequenceDiagram
 29:     autonumber
 30:     User->>PM: Request Figma to Webflow build
 31:     PM->>PM: Read CLAUDE.md and agentic runtime docs
 32:     PM->>Steward: Check workspace and handoff
 33:     PM->>Operator: Extract Figma raw data and content
 34:     Operator-->>PM: Write workspace/rawdata and workspace/contents
 35:     PM->>Architect: Create Client-First blueprint
 36:     Architect-->>PM: Write workspace/blueprints and page_structure.json
 37:     PM->>User: Present blueprint and stop for approval
 38:     User->>PM: Approved
 39:     PM->>Operator: Build in Webflow with MCP-352
 40:     Operator-->>PM: Write ReAct entries to workspace/state.json
 41:     PM->>Gatekeeper: Reflection review
 42:     Gatekeeper-->>PM: Pass, revise, or block
 43:     PM->>Architect: Run QA against real Webflow state
 44:     Architect-->>PM: APPROVED or FIX with evidence
 45:     PM->>Gatekeeper: Run local gates
 46:     Gatekeeper-->>PM: Readiness report
 47:     PM->>User: Evidence-backed completion report
 48: ```
 49: 
 50: ## Folder Map
 51: 
 52: ```text
 53: CLAUDE.md
 54: .claude/
 55:   agents/
 56:   skills/
 57: .user_versions/
 58:   VERSION_HISTORY.md
 59: .user_bugs-log/
 60: .user_guides/
 61: agentic/
 62:   specs/
 63:   schemas/
 64:   knowledge/
 65:   memory/
 66:   policies/
 67:   orchestration/
 68:   evals/
 69:   memory/team-memory.md
 70:   memory/session-handoff.md
 71:   orchestration/sop.md
 72:   policies/runtime-instructions.md
 73: scripts/
 74:   init_workspace.py
 75:   archive_workspace.py
 76:   restore_workspace.py
 77:   gates/
 78: tools/
 79:   utils.py
 80: knowledge-base/
 81:   client-first-theory.md
 82: workspace/       # generated runtime state, gitignored
 83: archives/        # generated backups, gitignored
 84: ```
 85: 
 86: ## Setup
 87: 
 88: Use Python 3.10 or newer.
 89: 
 90: ```cmd
 91: python scripts\init_workspace.py --project "Project Name" --figma "https://www.figma.com/design/file"
 92: python scripts\gates\validate_agentic_structure.py --target .
 93: python scripts\gates\run_quality_gate.py --target .
 94: python scripts\gates\scan_secrets.py --target .
 95: python scripts\gates\validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .
 96: python scripts\gates\validate_skills.py --target .
 97: python scripts\gates\validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .
 98: python scripts\gates\validate_phase_state.py --target .
 99: python scripts\gates\validate_relative_paths.py --target .
100: python scripts\gates\validate_client_first_library.py --target .
101: ```
102: 
103: Workspace lifecycle:
104: 
105: ```cmd
106: python scripts\archive_workspace.py
107: python scripts\restore_workspace.py
108: python scripts\restore_workspace.py 0
109: ```
110: 
111: ## Hard Rules
112: 
113: - Claude Code is the only intended agent runtime.
114: - Python scripts are the active automation path.
115: - The PM must stop after blueprint and wait for user approval.
116: - Webflow writes require target site/page confirmation and approval.
117: - Operator must use native Webflow element operations and MCP-352.
118: - `whtml_builder` is prohibited.
119: - REM units are mandatory.
120: - Figma properties must be mapped through `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` before class decisions are written into a blueprint.
121: - Workspace JSON evidence is mandatory for reports.
122: - Webflow action logs must include reason, action, observation, and next decision.
123: - Reflection review is required before risky phase closeout.
124: - QA approval requires actual Webflow state or snapshot evidence.
125: - No silent overwrite.
126: - Secrets must not be committed.
127: - Local filesystem paths in this folder must stay relative.
128: 
129: ## Standalone Readiness
130: 
131: The generated system spec is at `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md`.
132: 
133: Validation targets:
134: 
135: - Structure profile: standard pass.
136: - V3 quality target: 4.7.
137: - Hard gates: all pass.
</file>

