 1: # CLAUDE.md
 2: 
 3: This folder is a Claude Code-native agentic workspace for the MAS V3 Figma-to-Webflow workflow.
 4: 
 5: ## Read First
 6: 
 7: 1. Read `agentic/memory/team-memory.md` for the current agent team, invariants, and operating boundaries.
 8: 2. Read `agentic/policies/runtime-instructions.md` for the MAS V3 mandates adapted to Claude Code.
 9: 3. Read `agentic/orchestration/sop.md` before starting any Figma-to-Webflow run.
10: 4. Read `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md` for the standalone agent-system contract.
11: 5. Read `agentic/orchestration/reflection-loop.md` and `agentic/orchestration/phase-state-machine.md` before closing or changing phases.
12: 6. Read `agentic/policies/approval-gates.md` before using Webflow, Figma, file writes, archive/restore, or any external connector.
13: 
14: ## Common Commands
15: 
16: ```cmd
17: python scripts\init_workspace.py --project "Project Name" --figma "https://www.figma.com/design/file"
18: python scripts\gates\validate_agentic_structure.py --target .
19: python scripts\gates\run_quality_gate.py --target .
20: python scripts\gates\scan_secrets.py --target .
21: python scripts\gates\validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .
22: python scripts\gates\validate_skills.py --target .
23: python scripts\gates\validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .
24: python scripts\gates\validate_phase_state.py --target .
25: python scripts\gates\validate_relative_paths.py --target .
26: ```
27: 
28: Workspace lifecycle:
29: 
30: ```cmd
31: python scripts\archive_workspace.py
32: python scripts\restore_workspace.py
33: python scripts\restore_workspace.py 0
34: ```
35: 
36: ## Operating Rules
37: 
38: - Never silently overwrite existing files.
39: - Never delete or restore `workspace/` unless the archive/restore safety gates pass.
40: - Never proceed from Blueprint to Webflow build until the user approves.
41: - Never use `whtml_builder`; build with Webflow native element operations and MCP-352.
42: - Always use REM units for spacing, sizes, and typography.
43: - Always record evidence in workspace JSON files before reporting progress.
44: - Always record Webflow actions with reason, action, observation, and next decision.
45: - Always run QA from real Webflow state or snapshots; do not guess visual parity.
46: - Treat `agentic/evals/standalone-architecture-baseline.md` as the local architecture baseline.
47: - Use `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` before mapping Figma properties to Webflow classes.
48: - Use Python as the project automation language.
49: - Keep local filesystem references relative inside this folder.
50: 
51: ## Workflow Summary
52: 
53: 1. `@pm` receives the user request and checks `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md`, `agentic/orchestration/sop.md`, and workspace state.
54: 2. `@operator` extracts Figma/raw data into `workspace/rawdata/` and `workspace/contents/`.
55: 3. `@architect` produces Client-First blueprints in `workspace/blueprints/`.
56: 4. `@pm` presents the blueprint and stops for approval.
57: 5. `@operator` builds in Webflow using MCP-352.
58: 6. `@gatekeeper` or `@architect` runs reflection review on risky artifacts.
59: 7. `@architect` runs QA against actual Webflow state and records fixes.
60: 8. `@pm` updates `agentic/memory/session-handoff.md` and reports evidence-backed completion.
